==English==
===Etymology===
From Latin ''[[lacrima]]'' {{f}}, '''tear''' + [[-osus]] "[[-full]]", from Old Latin [[dacruma]], from proto-indo-European *dakru-, cognate with English tear.

===Pronunciation===
